# --- Build-time bulk (toolchain, library SDKs, intermediates) -----------
# These are exactly the build-time-only directories. Anyone building from
# source has to supply them themselves; see README.md.
SFML-3.1.0/
imgui-master/
mingw64/
third_party/
build/

# Compile artifacts
*.o
*.obj
*.a.tmp
*.dat.tmp
*.txt.tmp

# Editor + OS noise
.vs/
.vscode/
.idea/
.cache/
Thumbs.db
Desktop.ini
.DS_Store

# Runtime state from running the app. The text *seed* files (menu.txt,
# inventory.txt, recipes.txt, tables.txt) are committed so a fresh clone has
# demo data immediately, but anything mutated at run time — binary records,
# logs, receipts, settings — must NOT be committed. The app re-seeds any
# missing file on first run, so users always get a working app.
dist/data/*.dat
dist/data/log.txt
dist/data/settings.txt
dist/data/receipts/*.txt
dist/data/receipts/*.pdf.txt
data/*.dat
data/log.txt
data/settings.txt
data/receipts/*.txt
data/receipts/*.pdf.txt

# Python build-time tooling
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# IMPORTANT: dist/, *.exe, and *.dll are NOT ignored. The runnable
# self-contained bundle MUST be committed (per project brief).
